        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer162517904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9873753826249007543"><b>&quot;Do you remember that story Anne Shirley used to tell long ago of the pupil who wanted to be a widow because if you were married your husband bossed you and if you weren&apos;t married people called you an old maid? Well, that is precisely my opinion. I&apos;d like to be a widow. Then I&apos;d have the freedom of the unmarried, with the kudos of the married. I could eat my cake and have it, too. Oh, to be a widow!&quot;</b><br/><br/> A collection of heartwarming tales set in Anne&apos;s neck of the woods. Though she has a speaking ro</span>
  <span id="freeText9873753826249007543" style="display:none"><b>"Do you remember that story Anne Shirley used to tell long ago of the pupil who wanted to be a widow because if you were married your husband bossed you and if you weren't married people called you an old maid? Well, that is precisely my opinion. I'd like to be a widow. Then I'd have the freedom of the unmarried, with the kudos of the married. I could eat my cake and have it, too. Oh, to be a widow!"</b><br /><br /> A collection of heartwarming tales set in Anne's neck of the woods. Though she has a speaking role in only one of the stories, her spirit and humor are present in all. A great many of the tales involve curmudgeonly old-timers of both sexes either falling in love for the first time, or rekindling the embers of long ago romances . . . a theme that never fails to bring a smile to my face.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9873753826249007543" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
