        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1256876361" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12498853040540235307">Reread again, Old Lady Loyds story will never fail to make me bawl. <br/>5/5<br/><br/>I just happened upon this and a few other L. M. Montgomery&apos;s in a charity shop today, vintage and almost good as new. Lucky bargain! <br/><br/>An absolute delight to read again. Its the kind of book I&apos;d call heartwarming without making the &quot;cringe&quot; face, because its so honestly is. Each short story was drawn well with distinctive characters with quirks and giggle worthy situations, long drawn romantic estrangements or sad fates, all wo</span>
  <span id="freeText12498853040540235307" style="display:none">Reread again, Old Lady Loyds story will never fail to make me bawl. <br />5/5<br /><br />I just happened upon this and a few other L. M. Montgomery's in a charity shop today, vintage and almost good as new. Lucky bargain! <br /><br />An absolute delight to read again. Its the kind of book I'd call heartwarming without making the "cringe" face, because its so honestly is. Each short story was drawn well with distinctive characters with quirks and giggle worthy situations, long drawn romantic estrangements or sad fates, all worth the read. Even the weaker stories were uplifting. <br /><br />The ones that made me cackle the most:<br />"Aunt Olivia's Beau"<br />"The Quarantine at Alexander Abraham's" <br /><br />The one that made me tear up the most (and there were a few) <br />"Old Lady Lloyd"<br /><br />There were a couple of stories that were more staunchly Christian, just in case you have a particular aversion to that you have been warned! As a Muslim, most of my values follow along a similar path, so I thought them sweet in sentiment. <br /><br />If you love a bit of old fashioned human nature and slice of life, this should be right up your garden path eyyyy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12498853040540235307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

