<div id="review_784126295" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/784126295" />
    <a title="Tara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1295593-tara"><img alt="Tara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1263008397p2/1295593.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/784126295?book_show_action=true">Dec 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara" href="/user/show/1295593-tara">Tara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer784126295" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7190149967203581239">If this hadn&apos;t been included in the Anne series on my Kindle, I may not have ever picked it up, thinking I was just about Avonlea&apos;d out. As it was, when Rilla was finished, I launched right into this. It is a series of short stories set around Avonlea, in to which Anne makes the occasional cameo appearance or mention, but otherwise is never a main character. I have to say LMM just has a delicious way of phrasing things sometimes, and there are a number of delightful passages and descriptions in </span>
  <span id="freeText7190149967203581239" style="display:none">If this hadn't been included in the Anne series on my Kindle, I may not have ever picked it up, thinking I was just about Avonlea'd out. As it was, when Rilla was finished, I launched right into this. It is a series of short stories set around Avonlea, in to which Anne makes the occasional cameo appearance or mention, but otherwise is never a main character. I have to say LMM just has a delicious way of phrasing things sometimes, and there are a number of delightful passages and descriptions in which she captures our human natures quite well. A frequent theme is marrying off hopeless old maids or rekindling love affairs years after old quarrels. In the near century that has gone by since these stories were set, much has changed in our culture, but not so much has changed in our nature. In these stories, you get to reflect upon that in a fun, quick read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7190149967203581239" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


